I once worked on a reporting feature where a SQL query fetching user activity logs was taking over 10 seconds to run.


My process was:
Analyzed the Query Plan:

I used EXPLAIN to review the query execution plan and found full table scans and missing indexes.
Reviewed Indexes:

I added composite indexes on the columns used in WHERE and ORDER BY clauses.
Optimized the Query:

I rewrote subqueries as joins and limited the result set with pagination.

Tested Performance:
After changes, the query time dropped to under 500ms.
Monitored in Production:
I set up slow query logging to catch regressions.